Meet Shawnee!
Shawnee has a sweet, soft face and a gentle personality to match! She enjoys going for walks with her person, walking elegantly by your side as you explore the neighborhood. As a German Shepherd dog, it's no surprise this girl is also a smarty who loves to work for.. treats! She knows Sit, 'Find it', and comes when called. Shawnee also likes to play fetch-- though her version is taken at a leisurely pace and she seems to enjoy relaxing and chewing the ball more
(**Scroll to see video!) üòâ
.
Shawnee came into the shelter on Oct 21, 2017 as an Owner Surrender. No reason for surrender was given, but they did report that she is housebroken, is friendly with small dogs (though fought with her GSD sibling), and is okay in the car and on leash. Shawnee is 5 years old and 85 pounds.
This lovable, friendly girl is ready to join a family on a lifetime of adventures- come meet her today!
üíñ Shawnee #A1736835 üêæ

We intruduce Lily, the first recipient of the @freethechi bandana. Repost @northcentralshelter. Say hello to sweet, little Lily!
Lily is an adorable, 8 pounds, 8 years old girl who is quite nervous in the shelter, but will be your adoring friend in exchange for treats and belly rubs. We believe she will thrive in a home that can help build her confidence and work on leash training. She seems to perk up when dogs are around and has been kenneled with other small dogs and done well.
Lily has been waiting at the shelter since Sept. 17, 2017 when she was surrendered with 3 other dogs (#A1729507 4 yrs old, female Chihuahua also still available).
She wants a home where she can cuddle in a warm bed, watch Netflix, eat all the treats, and chill! Not too much to ask for this little doe. Please share or come give Lily a home in time for the holidays!

@Regranned from @northcentralshelter - Meet Shawnee!
Shawnee has a sweet, soft face and a gentle personality to match! She enjoys going for walks with her person, walking elegantly by your side as you explore the neighborhood. As a German Shepherd dog, it's no surprise this girl is also a smarty who loves to work for.. treats! She knows Sit, 'Find it', and comes when called. Shawnee also likes to play fetch-- though her version is taken at a leisurely pace and she seems to enjoy relaxing and chewing the ball more
(**Scroll to see video!) üòâ
.
Shawnee came into the shelter on Oct 21, 2017 as an Owner Surrender. No reason for surrender was given, but they did report that she is housebroken, is friendly with small dogs (though fought with her GSD sibling), and is okay in the car and on leash. Shawnee is 5 years old and 85 pounds.
This lovable, friendly girl is ready to join a family on a lifetime of adventures- come meet her today!
